{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.24",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 24,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 24",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 24 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:1",
      "text": "“Why are not times of judgment kept by the Almighty, and why do those who know him never see his days?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:2",
      "text": "Men remove landmarks; they seize flocks and pasture them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:3",
      "text": "They drive away the ass of the fatherless; they take the widow's ox for a pledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:4",
      "text": "They thrust the poor off the road; the poor of the earth all hide themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:5",
      "text": "Behold, like wild asses in the desert they go forth to their toil, seeking prey in the wilderness as food for their children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:6",
      "text": "They gather their fodder in the field and they glean the vineyard of the wicked man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:7",
      "text": "They lie all night naked, without clothing, and have no covering in the cold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:8",
      "text": "They are wet with the rain of the mountains, and cling to the rock for want of shelter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:9",
      "text": "(There are those who snatch the fatherless child from the breast, and take in pledge the infant of the poor.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:10",
      "text": "They go about naked, without clothing; hungry, they carry the sheaves;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:11",
      "text": "among the olive rows of the wicked they make oil; they tread the wine presses, but suffer thirst.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:12",
      "text": "From out of the city the dying groan, and the soul of the wounded cries for help; yet God pays no attention to their prayer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:13",
      "text": "“There are those who rebel against the light, who are not acquainted with its ways, and do not stay in its paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:14",
      "text": "The murderer rises in the dark, that he may kill the poor and needy; and in the night he is as a thief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:15",
      "text": "The eye of the adulterer also waits for the twilight, saying, ‘No eye will see me’; and he disguises his face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:16",
      "text": "In the dark they dig through houses; by day they shut themselves up; they do not know the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:17",
      "text": "For deep darkness is morning to all of them; for they are friends with the terrors of deep darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:18",
      "text": "“You say, ‘They are swiftly carried away upon the face of the waters; their portion is cursed in the land; no treader turns toward their vineyards.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:19",
      "text": "Drought and heat snatch away the snow waters; so does Sheol those who have sinned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:20",
      "text": "The squares of the town forget them; their name is no longer remembered; so wickedness is broken like a tree.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:21",
      "text": "“They feed on the barren childless woman, and do no good to the widow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:22",
      "text": "Yet God prolongs the life of the mighty by his power; they rise up when they despair of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:23",
      "text": "He gives them security, and they are supported; and his eyes are upon their ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:24",
      "text": "They are exalted a little while, and then are gone; they wither and fade like the mallow; they are cut off like the heads of grain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.24.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 24:25",
      "text": "If it is not so, who will prove me a liar, and show that there is nothing in what I say?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
